Cell.data: Surface Flooding Risk: Number of manholes where water surface elevation is < 2 feet from ground surface elevation
Basement Sewer Backup Risk: Number of parcels where hydraulic grade line is < 8 feet from estimated finished floor elevation

Pipe Surcharge Risk: Length of pipe in miles (number of segments) that meet two conditions: (1) surcharge lasts 30 minutes or longer and also (2) the peak hydraulic grade line is > 4 feet above the pipe crown
Pipe Capacity: Length of pipe in miles (number of segments) with peak flow to design flow ratio > 1.2
Pump Stations: Number of pump stations where firm pumping capacity is insufficient to convey expected design flow

Footer.footerText: Basement elevation is estimated at 8 feet below finished floor elevation of the parcel.
These are considered to be hydraulically deficient pipes; operating under these conditions is detrimental to pipe integrity.
Pump stations that have firm capacity less than expected peak inflow but safely store excess flow in the collection system are not included.
